column5: I just thought I'd share this pic of a thirty inch walleye I caught and released near little Chamberlain today. Cheers to my guest John as he made a heroic netjob, as my hooked popped out. He was rewarded later on with a 27.5 himself. We boated many eyes today, with at least thirty being over the slot. Post spawn is started to shine!http://photobucket.com/Colinthirtyinch
Great Fish!!! Nice work on the net job too.Where is little Chamberlain?LoDo
Great fish Colin. I'd love to see one hit the thirty inch mark on my fishboard soon With this one, and the 33" you got earlier, you're off to a great start on the season. Awesome buddy.
Congrats guys and thanks for sharing. Good friends and Canada fishing- does it get any better then that??
